---
import SeoLandingLayout from "../components/SeoLandingLayout.astro";

const page = {
  title: "What Makeup Looks Good on Me? AI Makeup Try-On",
  description:
    "Upload a selfie to preview makeup directions for your face. Use AI makeup try-on to compare colors, styles, and before-and-after references before buying products.",
  heroImage: "/images/article-ai-tryon-comparison.webp",
  ogImage: "/images/article-ai-tryon-comparison.webp",
  faq: [
    {
      q: "How does AI makeup try-on work?",
      a: "AI Beauty Stylist uses your selfie and selected style to create a visual makeup preview. It is best used as a decision aid for color, intensity, and placement, not as a guarantee of the exact result you will get with real products.",
    },
    {
      q: "What makeup looks good on me?",
      a: "Start by comparing your skin tone, undertone, eye shape, face shape, and the situation you are dressing for. The try-on preview helps you narrow the direction before you follow a tutorial or buy a product.",
    },
    {
      q: "Is my photo stored or shared?",
      a: "Your photo is used only to provide the analysis or try-on you request and is automatically deleted no later than 30 days. We do not use uploaded selfies for model training without separate authorization. You can delete related results and records from the product.",
    },
    {
      q: "How many styles can I try on for free?",
      a: "Free accounts get 3 complete diagnosis sessions per month. You can earn additional free tries by sharing your before-and-after results on social media (one share = one extra try, up to once per day).",
    },
    {
      q: "Is the try-on realistic?",
      a: "The preview is designed to reflect your face shape, skin tone, and feature proportions more closely than a generic filter. Real product texture, lighting, skin prep, and application skill can still change the final look.",
    },
  ],
  relatedLinks: [
    { label: "Soft Glam Makeup", url: "/looks/soft-glam" },
    { label: "Natural Makeup Look", url: "/looks/natural-makeup" },
    { label: "Interview Makeup", url: "/scenarios/interview" },
    { label: "Date Night Makeup", url: "/looks/date-night" },
    { label: "Makeup for Beginners", url: "/guides/beginner-tutorial" },
  ],
};
---

<SeoLandingLayout {...page}>
  <Fragment slot="hero">
    <h1>What Makeup Looks Good on Me? Try It on Your Face First</h1>
    <p>
      Upload a selfie and compare makeup directions on your own face before you
      buy products or copy a tutorial. Use the preview to decide color,
      intensity, and placement with less guessing.
    </p>
  </Fragment>

  <div class="seo-content">
    <h2>Why Try-On Beats Guessing</h2>
    <p>
      Most makeup decisions are educated guesses. You buy a lipstick because it
      looks great on someone else, only to find it clashes with your undertone.
      You follow a tutorial that's designed for hooded eyes when yours are
      deep-set. The result? Disappointment, wasted money, and a drawer full of
      "maybe someday" products.
    </p>
    <p>
      AI makeup try-on reduces that guesswork. Before you buy anything or spend
      twenty minutes on a tutorial, you can compare how a style direction reads
      on <strong>your</strong> face. It is a preview for decision-making, not a promise
      that every product will apply the same way in real life.
    </p>

    <h2>How It Works</h2>
    <div class="step-list">
      <div class="step-card">
        <div class="step-num">1</div>
        <div>
          <h4>Upload Your Selfie</h4>
          <p>
            Take a clear photo of your face in natural light. No makeup needed —
            bare face works best.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-card">
        <div class="step-num">2</div>
        <div>
          <h4>AI Analyzes Your Features</h4>
          <p>
            The AI uses your visible features to estimate useful makeup
            directions: tone, contrast, eye shape, face shape, and feature
            balance.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-card">
        <div class="step-num">3</div>
        <div>
          <h4>Pick a Style to Try On</h4>
          <p>
            Choose from soft glam, natural, date night, interview — or browse
            40+ styles in our catalog.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-card">
        <div class="step-num">4</div>
        <div>
          <h4>See Your Personalized Result</h4>
          <p>
            The AI generates a visual reference showing how that style direction
            could read on your face.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>Try-On vs. Photo Filter: The Difference</h2>
    <div class="highlight-box">
      <p>
        Filters apply the same overlay to every face. AI try-on adapts the
        makeup direction to your face shape, skin tone, and natural coloring. It
        still needs real-world judgment for product texture, lighting, and
        application.
      </p>
    </div>

    <table class="compare-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th></th>
          <th>AI Try-On</th>
          <th>Photo Filter</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Adapts to your face</td>
          <td>Yes</td>
          <td>No — same overlay</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Considers skin tone</td>
          <td>Yes</td>
          <td>No</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Helps compare finish direction</td>
          <td>Yes — as a visual reference</td>
          <td>Often exaggerated</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Helps you buy the right products</td>
          <td>Yes — includes product recommendations</td>
          <td>No</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Privacy-focused</td>
          <td>Photo auto-deleted in 30 days</td>
          <td>Varies by app</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>What You Get After Try-On</h2>
    <p>Once you see a style you like, the platform gives you three things:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Personalized tutorial</strong> — a step-by-step guide showing how
        to recreate the look on your own face, with tips for your specific features.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Product recommendations</strong> — real SKUs matched to your skin
        tone and budget (drugstore to high-end).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Before-and-after preview</strong> — a comparison you can save or share
        when you want feedback.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Try It Free</h2>
    <p>
      You get 3 free try-on sessions per month — enough to validate that the
      output actually works for your face. If it does, upgrade to Pro for
      unlimited access.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="seo-cta" slot="cta">
    <div class="seo-cta-inner">
      <h2>Ready to See How You Look?</h2>
      <p>
        Upload your selfie, pick a style, and compare a makeup direction before
        you spend time or money on it.
      </p>
      <a href="/tryon" class="cta-btn">Try AI Makeup Try-On — Free</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="seo-related" slot="related">
    <div class="related-inner">
      <h3>Explore More</h3>
      <ul class="related-list">
        {
          page.relatedLinks.map((link) => (
            <li>
              <a href={link.url}>{link.label}</a>
            </li>
          ))
        }
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</SeoLandingLayout>
